                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18110403-41-victim385 t18110403-41-viclabel237"></join>. On the 22d of<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181104030018"></xptr>February last, about eight o'clock in the evening suspecting the prisoner having part of my property on his person, I searched him, in his hat I found two pieces of printed callico, which had been taken from pieces in my possession, I sent for a constable and had him sent to prison. The prisoner is my apprentice.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I only cut one piece off, the other damaged pieces were in the box, I always thought the damaged pieces were allowed to the apprentice.</p>
               <p>The prisoner called six witnesses, who gave him a good character.</p>
